Visulization challenge in R - Changes in Highest Educational Attainment in the U.S

library(gapminder)
library(here)
library(socviz)
library(tidyverse)
library(viridis)
library(ggrepel)
library(reshape)

Let’s replicate a plot within 1 hour!

The underlying data set is called edu in the socviz package.
We are going to recreate this visualization, with the goal of creating as close of a replica as possible. Have a fun!

theme_set(theme_minimal())
head(edu)
## # A tibble: 6 × 11
##   age   sex    year total elem4 elem8   hs3   hs4 coll3 coll4 median
##   <chr> <chr> <int> <int> <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 25-34 Male   2016 21845   116   468  1427  6386  6015  7432     NA
## 2 25-34 Male   2015 21427   166   488  1584  6198  5920  7071     NA
## 3 25-34 Male   2014 21217   151   512  1611  6323  5910  6710     NA
## 4 25-34 Male   2013 20816   161   582  1747  6058  5749  6519     NA
## 5 25-34 Male   2012 20464   161   579  1707  6127  5619  6270     NA
## 6 25-34 Male   2011 20985   190   657  1791  6444  5750  6151     NA
edu$high_rate <- edu$hs4/edu$total
edu$coll_rate <- edu$coll4/edu$total

clean_data <- data.frame(edu[, c(1,2,3,12,13)])
clean_data <- melt(clean_data, id.vars = names(clean_data)[1:3])
colnames(clean_data)[4] <- "Edu_level"
colnames(clean_data)[5] <- "Percent"
clean_data$Edu_level <- factor(clean_data$Edu_level, levels = rev(levels(clean_data$Edu_level)))
clean_data$age <- factor(clean_data$age, levels = c("25-34", "35-54", "55>"),
                  labels = c("Ages 25 to 34", "Ages 35 to 54", "Ages 55 or Older")
                  )
colors = c("#420a85", "#ffe400")
plot <- ggplot(aes(x = year, y = Percent, group = sex), data = clean_data)+
  geom_line(aes(group = Edu_level, color = Edu_level), size = 0.8)+
  facet_grid(sex ~ age, switch="y") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 5L))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(1940, 1959, 1978, 1997, 2016))+
  scale_color_manual(labels = c("College\nGraduate", "High School\nGraduate"), values = colors)+
  geom_text_repel(data = subset(clean_data, year == '2016' & Edu_level == "high_rate"), aes(label = round(100* Percent,1)), color = "#ffe400",size = 4, segment.color = NA, nudge_x = 30, nudge_y = -0.02, fontface = "bold") +
   geom_text_repel(data = subset(clean_data, year == '2016' & Edu_level == "coll_rate"), aes(label = round(100* Percent,1)), color = "#420a85", size = 4, segment.color = NA, nudge_x = 30, nudge_y = 0.02, fontface = "bold") +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "Percent of Respondents",
       title = "Changes in Highest Educational Attainment in the U.S.",
       subtitle = "From 1940 to 2016, disaggregated by gender",
       caption = "Data source: US Census Bureau, via 'sociz' package")+
  theme(panel.spacing=unit(0.4, "in"), plot.title = element_text(size= 14), plot.subtitle = element_text(size=12), 
        axis.text.x = element_text(face = "bold"), axis.text.y = element_text(face = "bold"),
        axis.title.x = element_text(face = "bold", size = 17), axis.title.y = element_text(face = "bold",size = 17),
        legend.position = "top", legend.title = element_text(size = 12), legend.text = element_text(size = 8),
        strip.text.x = element_text(face = "bold", size = 10), strip.text.y = element_text(face = "bold"), strip.placement = "outside",
        panel.border = element_rect(colour = "black", fill = NA))+
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Education Level"))

ggsave("Wang, Qingwen_final.pdf", plot= plot, width = 11, height = 8.5, units = "in")
